annotationA: G protein-coupled receptor kinase 2 (Gprk2) is a member of a family of serine/threonine kinases that modulate G-protein coupled receptors. It is required for female fertility, normal egg shape, and normal egg cAMP levels. Gprk2 is also implicated in Hedgehog signaling and olfactory rhythmicity; Belongs to the protein kinase superfamily. AGC Ser/Thr protein kinase family. GPRK subfamily
annotationB: G protein-coupled receptor kinase 1; Specifically phosphorylates the activated forms of G protein-coupled receptors
